FTPD(8)

NAME
    ftpd - SmallOS FTP server

SYNOPSIS
    ftpd [--quiet|--no-log] [--log-file path]

DESCRIPTION
    ftpd starts a single-session FTP server listening on 0.0.0.0:2121.

    The server uses / as its FTP root. The built-in account is:

        user: ftp
        pass: ftp

    Passive data connections use port 30000. When running under QEMU user
    networking, forward both host port 2121 and host port 30000 if you want
    to connect from the host.

OPTIONS
    --quiet
        Disable service logging and close standard output and standard error.

    --no-log
        Alias for --quiet.

    --log-file path
        Append service output to path. The default log path is
        /var/log/ftpd.log.

FILES
    /var/log/ftpd.log
        Default service log.

NOTES
    ftpd currently allows read, write, delete, and mkdir operations for the
    built-in FTP user.

SEE ALSO
    cserve(8)
